== Land Use == Due to its location within the {{ill|city area|ja|市街地|12=draft}}, the Utsunomiya Hills have been developed for various purposes, including {{ill|shrines|ja|神社|12=draft}}, {{ill|parks|ja|公園|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Utsunomiya Velodrome|ja|宇都宮競輪場|12=draft}}, residential areas, {{ill|schools|ja|学校|12=draft}}, and cemeteries. It is also an area of historical significance, with numerous archaeological sites from the {{ill|Paleolithic period in Japan|ja|旧石器時代|12=draft}} onwards. The region contains several {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|12=draft}} clusters, including the {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yaguchiyama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nagaoka Hundred Caves Kofun|ja|長岡百穴古墳|1=Nagaoka Hundred Caves|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Kawazuka Kofun Group|ja|瓦塚古墳群|12=draft}}.<ref name="Shibuya et al. 2019">{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|pp=2-4}}</ref>
