{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11449703]] Wikidata name: Utsunomiya Hills [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:18, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} [[File:20070204宇都宮丘陵Tagged.jpg|thumb|right|300px|The right side shows the Utsunomiya Hills.]] '''Utsunomiya Hills''' (宇都宮丘陵) refers to a series of [[:en:Hügelland|hills]] located in [[:en:Utsunomiya|Utsunomiya]], [[:en:Tochigi Prefecture|Tochigi Prefecture]], stretching northward from the central city area.
== Overview == The Utsunomiya Hills are one of the branching ridges extending in a dendritic pattern from the {{ill|Taishaku Mountain Range|ja|帝釈山脈|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taishaku Mountain Range|qq=}} and the {{ill|Ashio Mountains|ja|足尾山地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashio Mountains|qq=}} toward the [[:en:Kantō Plain|Kantō Plain]].<ref name="Shibuya et al. 2019">{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=2}}</ref> Viewed from the city, the hills begin at {{ill|Myōjin-yama (Utsunomiya)|ja|明神山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin-yama (Utsunomiya)|qq=}}, near the [[Utsunomiya Futarayama Shrine]], and extend northward through {{ill|Hachiman-yama (Utsunomiya)|ja|八幡山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman-yama (Utsunomiya)|qq=}} to {{ill|Tomatsuri-yama|ja|戸祭山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomatsuri-yama|qq=}}. The foothills are flanked by the {{ill|Tagawa River (Tonegawa Basin)|ja|田川 (利根川水系)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tagawa River (Tonegawa Basin)|qq=}} to the east and the {{ill|Kamagawa River|ja|釜川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamagawa River|qq=}} to the west.
The bedrock of the hills consists of [[:en:Tuff|tuff]], a type of stone quarried as Nagaoka Stone, which is considered a variant of [[:en:Ōya stone|Ōya Stone]].<ref name="Shibuya et al. 2019"/> The surface is covered by layers of [[:en:Loam|loam]], [[:en:Pumice|pumice]], and other [[:en:Ejecta|volcanic ejecta]].<ref name="Shibuya et al. 2019"/>
== Land Use == Due to its location within the {{ill|city area|ja|市街地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/city area|qq=}}, the Utsunomiya Hills have been developed for various purposes, including [[:en:Shinto shrine|shrines]], [[:en:Park|parks]], the [[:en:Utsunomiya Velodrome|Utsunomiya Velodrome]], residential areas, [[:en:School|schools]], and cemeteries. It is also an area of historical significance, with numerous archaeological sites from the [[:en:Paleolithic|Paleolithic period in Japan]] onwards. The region contains several [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] clusters, including the {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=}}, {{ill|Yaguchiyama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yaguchiyama Kofun|qq=}}, {{ill|Nagaoka Hundred Caves Kofun|ja|長岡百穴古墳|1=Nagaoka Hundred Caves|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagaoka Hundred Caves Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagaoka Hundred Caves|qq=}}, and {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun Group|lt=Kawarazuka Kofun Group|lt=Kawazuka Kofun Group|ja|瓦塚古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawazuka Kofun Group|qq=}}.<ref name="Shibuya et al. 2019">{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|pp=2-4}}</ref>
